[1] Cholera - Burundi
Date: Thu 20 Jan 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Sunday Times, South Africa [edited]
<http://www.sundaytimes.co.za/zones/sundaytimesNEW/basket6st/basket6st1106224611.aspx>

Cholera outbreak claims 3 in Burundi
-----------------------------------------
A cholera outbreak in the Burundi capital of Bujumbura is thought to have
claimed 3 lives, with more cases being reported daily, said Medinfo in
Johannesburg.
Dr. Andrew Jamieson said the epidemic, which started on 12 Jan 2005, was
spreading rapidly. "We think 3 people have already died, but this has not
yet been substantiated," he said.
He said 88 cases had been reported by the Ministry of Public Health since
the outbreak. He attributed the "flare up" of the disease to the heavy
rainfall that caused fecal contamination of ground water and wells, and the
cutting off of public water sources in informal settlements due to
non-payment for water by the city council to the water utility company.
Jamieson advised travelers to the region to practice good food and water
hygiene and to consider immunization against cholera if at high risk.
--
