[3] Diarrhea - Indonesia
Date: Fri 21 Jan 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Jakarta Post [edited]
<http://www.thejakartapost.com/detailnational.asp?fileid=20050120.D08&irec=15>

Diarrhea victims flood hospitals
-------------------------------
The number of people suffering from diarrhea is on the rise in Surabaya,
with Dr. Mohammad Soewandi Hospital treating over 65 children in the 1st
week of January 2005 and 49 more in the 2nd week.
The hospital's secretary, Sukadji, said the January 2005 figure was higher
than in December 2004, but less compared to the October-November 2004
period when the hospital treated 1540 patients with diarrhea. Out of the
1540 patients, 1121 of them were children.
Most diarrhea patients were treated and released after 2 or 3 days, he said.
In Dr. Soetomo Hospital, an average of 13 diarrhea patients have been
admitted each day in January 2005
--
